erns. I'm noting the hierarchical relationships.\n\n\n**Defining Data Structures**\n\nI'm now focusing on defining the data structures within the `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS` table. Specifically, I am structuring documents, invoices metadata, support tickets, and governance items. I am taking care to identify their unique keys and attributes for each entity type. This involves carefully mapping the attributes such as `title`, `amount_usd`, `subject`, `control_name` and keys like `PK`, `SK`, `GSI1PK`, `GSI1SK`.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T20:38:12.520Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"ypok3wna","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/docs/PHASE_6_AWS_FINAL_SETUP.md","new_text":"# GFF AI Platform: Phase 6 AWS Production Deployment & Data Modeling Guide\n\nThis document defines the enterprise AWS cloud migration strategy for the **GFF AI Platform** from the local Phase 5 sandbox. It specifies the exact schemas for three required DynamoDB tables, an S3 storage bucket, and the required environment parameters.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Cloud-Native Serverless Architecture\n\n```\n+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                               PHASE 6 ENTERPRISE AWS TOPOLOGY                                  |\n|  [ SECURE CLIENTS ] ==( HTTPS / TLS 1.3 )==> [ API GATEWAY ] ==> [ FASTAPI ON AWS LAMBDA ]    |\n|                                                                          |                     |\n|  [ S3 STORAGE BUCKET ] <--(Presigned URLs)-------------------------------+                     |\n|  (gff-portal-documents)                                                  v                     |\n|                                                                 [ AMAZON DYNAMODB ]            |\n|                                                                 - GFF_USERS                    |\n|                                                                 - GFF_CLIENTS                  |\n|                                                                 - GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS             |\n+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Production DynamoDB Data Modeling\n\nExactly **three** DynamoDB tables are used. Complex workspace and transactional entities are modeled inside a single-table architecture (`GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`) using custom Partition Keys (`PK`) and Sort Keys (`SK`).\n\n### 2.1. Table Map Overview\n| Table Name | Partition Key (PK) | Sort Key (SK) | Global Secondary Index (GSI) | Purpose |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **`GFF_USERS`** | `email` (String) | *None* | *None* | Global user registry, credentials, and organizational access. |\n| **`GFF_CLIENTS`** | `client_id` (String) | *None* | *None* | Enterprise customer accounts and service-level profiles. |\n| **`GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`** | `PK` (String) | `SK` (String) | `GSI1` (using `GSI1PK` & `GSI1SK`) | High-performance single-table store for multi-tenant records. |\n\n---\n\n### 2.2. Table Definition: `GFF_USERS`\n*   **Table Name**: `GFF_USERS`\n*   **Primary Key**: `email` (String)\n*   **Example Item**:\n```json\n{\n  \"email\": \"executive.admin@client.com\",\n  \"full_name\": \"Alexander Sterling\",\n  \"role\": \"admin\",\n  \"client_id\": \"client_gff_corp_01\",\n  \"status\": \"ACTIVE\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-06-28T12:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.3. Table Definition: `GFF_CLIENTS`\n*   **Table Name**: `GFF_CLIENTS`\n*   **Primary Key**: `client_id` (String)\n*   **Example Item**:\n```json\n{\n  \"client_id\": \"client_gff_corp_01\",\n  \"company_name\": \"Sovereign Logistics Corp\",\n  \"industry\": \"Supply Chain\",\n  \"tier\": \"ENTERPRISE\",\n  \"status\": \"ACTIVE\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-01-15T08:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.4. Single-Table Definition: `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`\n*   **Table Name**: `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`\n*   **Primary Key**: `PK` (String), `SK` (String)\n*   **GSI Name**: `GSI1` (using partition key `GSI1PK` and sort key `GSI1SK`)\n*   **Purpose**: Single-table design housing the 6 core operational models of the GFF AI Portal.\n\n#### Entity Mappings & Storage Patterns\n\n1. **Projects**\n   - **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>`\n   - **`SK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>`\n   - **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>`\n   - **`GSI1SK`**: `METADATA`\n   - **Attributes**: `name`, `status`, `progress`, `budget`, `created_at`\n\n2. **AI Operations**\n   - **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>`\n   - **`SK`**: `AIOPS#<ops_id>`\n   - **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>` (associates AI workflows to parent project)\n   - **`GSI1SK`**: `AIOPS#<ops_id>`\n   - **Attributes**: `name`, `status`, `agent_count`, `runtime_seconds`, `cpu_usage`, `memory_usage`\n\n3. **Documents Metadata**\n   - **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>`\n   - **`SK`**: `DOC#<doc_id>`\n   - **`GSI1PK`**: `PROJ#<project_id>` (allows retrieving files by project workspace)\n   - **`GSI1SK`**: `DOC#<doc_id>`\n   - **Attributes**: `title`, `s3_key`, `file_size`, `category`, `uploaded_by`, `uploaded_at`\n\n4. **Invoices Metadata**\n   - **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>`\n   - **`SK`**: `INV#<invoice_id>`\n   - **`GSI1PK`**: `BILLING_PERIOD#<year_month>` (enables monthly cross-client compile queries)\n   - **`GSI1SK`**: `INV#<invoice_id>`\n   - **Attributes**: `amount_usd`, `status`, `due_date`, `epochs_consumed`, `created_at`\n\n5. **Support Tickets**\n   - **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>`\n   - **`SK`**: `TICKET#<ticket_id>`\n   - **`GSI1PK`**: `STATUS#<status_code>` (supports status-based dashboard queues)\n   - **`GSI1SK`**: `TICKET#<ticket_id>`\n   - **Attributes**: `subject`, `priority`, `status_text`, `assigned_to`, `created_at`\n\n6. **Governance Items**\n   - **`PK`**: `CLIENT#<client_id>`\n   - **`SK`**: `GOV#<gov_id>`\n   - **`GSI1PK`**: `STANDARD#<compliance_standard>` (enables standard-specific queries e.g., SOC2)\n   - **`GSI1SK`**: `GOV#<gov_id>`\n   - **Attributes**: `control_name`, `status` (PASSED/FAILED), `remediation_notes`, `assessed_at`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Cloud Object Storage Setup (Amazon S3)\n\n*   **Bucket Reference**: `gff-portal-documents-prod`\n*   **Security Configurations**:\n    *   **Block Public Access**: Enabled.\n    *   **Encryption at Rest**: Enforced using KMS customer-managed keys (SSE-KMS).\n    *   **Secure Transport**: Restricts transport to TLS 1.3/HTTPS.\n    *   **Presigned Access**: The portal frontend uploads/downloads assets using short-lived cryptographically signed pre-signed URLs generated by Lambda (valid for 15 minutes).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Required Deployment Environment Keys\n\n### 4.1. Next.js Frontend Keys (`.env.production`)\n```env\nNEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://api.gff.ai/v1\nNEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ENV=production\nNEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_UPLOADS_ENABLED=true\nNEXT_PUBLIC_S3_BUCKET_NAME=gff-portal-documents-prod\n```\n\n### 4.2. FastAPI AWS Backend Keys (`backend/prod.env` / Lambda Variables)\n```env\nPROJECT_NAME=\"GFF AI Enterprise Cloud Engine\"\nAPI_V1_STR=\"/api/v1\"\nENVIRONMENT=\"production\"\nCORS_ORIGINS=\"https://portal.gff.ai,https://admin.gff.ai\"\nAWS_REGION=us-east-1\nDYNAMODB_TABLE_USERS=GFF_USERS\nDYNAMODB_TABLE_CLIENTS=GFF_CLIENTS\nDYNAMODB_TABLE_PORTAL_ITEMS=GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS\nS3_BUCKET_PORTAL_DOCUMENTS=gff-portal-documents-prod\nJWT_SECRET=production_cryptographically_secure_256_bit_signature_key_2026\nACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=60\n```\n"}}}
