{"ts":"2026-06-27T20:38:40.180Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"n6ej6doz","input":{"summary":"Created the Phase 6 AWS Production Deployment & Data Modeling Guide at docs/PHASE_6_AWS_FINAL_SETUP.md. The guide defines the AWS serverless architecture (API Gateway, Lambda, S3, DynamoDB) and documents exactly three DynamoDB tables: GFF_USERS (partition key: email), GFF_CLIENTS (partition key: client_id), and GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS (PK, SK, and GSI1 using GSI1PK and GSI1SK). The single-table layout of GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS maps out Projects, AI Operations, Documents metadata, Invoices metadata, Support Tickets, and Governance Items. It also outlines the configuration for one secure private S3 bucket (gff-portal-documents-prod) and provides the precise Next.js frontend and FastAPI backend environment keys required for a production AWS stack.","verified":true}}}
